  "texts": [
    "As LLM technology continues to evolve, it is anticipated that these methods will become increasingly reliable and find broader applications, thereby overcoming the current limitations of direct human evaluation.",
    "Objective evaluationObjective evaluation refers to assessing the capabilities of LLM-based autonomous agents using quantitative metrics that can be computed, compared and tracked over time.",
    "In contrast to subjective evaluation, objective metrics aim to provide concrete, measurable insights into the agent performance.",
    "For conducting objective evaluation, there are three important aspects, that is, the evaluation metrics, protocols and benchmarks.",
    "In the following, we introduce these aspects more in detail.Metrics: In order to objectively evaluate the effectiveness of the agents, designing proper metrics is significant, which may influence the evaluation accuracy and comprehensiveness."
  ],
